messages.message:
Probably the pettiest thing I’ll raise, sorry:
• User is looking for `settings`
• Click on `?` - open “Provide Feedback”
• user might think “oh must be the book icon, as opposed to the user initials in the corner”
• clicks on Book.. opens new tab.. annoyed user.
I think what I’m saying is the `?` is unclear that it’s feedback and not support/settings.
The Book icon behaviour is not consistent with the rest of the icons
we should have tooltips for these
Yea, we should almost always have tooltips or other forms of text accompanying icons
